TITLE: Jemele Hill accuses Asians of 'carrying the water for white supremacy' for backing affirmative action decision
SUMMARY: The Atlantic writer Jemele Hill accused Asian Americans of “carrying water" for White supremacy by celebrating the Supreme Court decision against affirmative action.

TITLE: Biden admin gets burned after considering study to 'block the sun'
SUMMARY: Twitter users expressed confusion over a released document revealing that the Biden administration is studying how to block sunlight to prevent climate change.

TITLE: Max Homa nails hole-in-one at Rocket Mortgage Classic
SUMMARY: Max Homa sunk a hole-in-one at the Rocket Mortgage Classic in Detroit Sunday, and he finished with a 67 in the final round. He finished the tournament tied for 21st.

TITLE: South Carolina plane crash near golf course leaves at least one dead, others injured
SUMMARY: At least one person is dead and several others are injured after a single-engine Piper PA-32 crashed in North Myrtle Beach, South Carolina, Sunday morning.

TITLE: Buttigieg claims Lorie Smith 'went into wedding business' only to provoke 'case like this' after SCOTUS ruling
SUMMARY: Pete Buttigieg told CNN on Sunday that Lorie Smith, the graphic designer who sued Colorado over their anti-discrimination law, just wanted to provoke "cases like this."

TITLE: ‘The Flash’ star Ezra Miller releases statement regarding lifting of temporary harassment order
SUMMARY: Ezra Miller released a statement regarding the recent expiration of a temporary harassment order against "The Flash" star. It was filed by a parent on behalf of their 12-year-old child.

TITLE: Rickie Fowler captures first PGA Tour win since 2019 at Rocket Mortgage Classic
SUMMARY: Rickie Fowler has finally captured his first PGA Tour win since 2019, beating Adam Hadwin and Collin Morikawa in a playoff hole to win the Rocket Mortgage Classic.

TITLE: Enough! French police unions condemn 'savage hordes,' forcing Macron into action
SUMMARY: Defying all odds against overwhelming numbers of rioters, French police officers are curtailing the violence and have compelled the French political establishment to stand behind them.

TITLE: Joe Biden takes Hunter to Camp David two weekends in a row amid scandal
SUMMARY: President Biden traveled with Hunter Biden to Camp David for the second weekend in a row Friday, just days after the DOJ announced a tentative plea agreement for the first son.

TITLE: Former Director of National Intelligence warns there's a 'cultural problem' within the DOJ
SUMMARY: Former Director of National Intelligence John Ratcliffe discusses the latest on the "disparity in treatment" by the Department of Justice.

TITLE: Tom Brady sticks to strict diet regimen even after retirement
SUMMARY: Tom Brady revealed in a recent interview he is sticking to the strict diet that helped him stay healthy through most of his career. He retired in February.

TITLE: Human remains found in barrel floating on South Carolina lake: police
SUMMARY: South Carolina man Eric Fetzer was arrested after human remains were found in a barrel floating on Lake Thicketty in upstate South Carolina, police said.

TITLE: Should I leave my VPN on 24/7?
SUMMARY: VPNs can be a great service to protecting your private info when traveling or using public Wi-Fi. Kurt "Cyberguy" Knutsson lays his out his best practices.

TITLE: South Korea draws hard line on North Korean aid, no longer a 'support department' for dictatorship
SUMMARY: South Korea ordered its Unification Ministry to shift its directives away from "support" for North Korea toward combatting its human rights abuses.

TITLE: US Army soldiers deployed to Middle East save mama dog and 8 newborn pups
SUMMARY: U.S. Army soldiers are caring for a mama dog and her eight pups who were saved from a rare ice storm in the Middle East. Nonprofit Paws of War is working to bring the dogs to America.

TITLE: Syria claims to shoot down Israeli missile strike as anti-aircraft debris lands in Israeli town
SUMMARY: Syria claims to have shot down Israeli missiles targeting air defense batteries near the city of Hom, with Israel saying no warplanes were damaged.

TITLE: NASCAR contractor dies of electrocution setting up Chicago Street Race
SUMMARY: A 53-year-old man who was hired as a contractor to set up audio equipment for the NASCAR Cup Series' Chicago Street Race on Sunday, has died after being electrocuted.

TITLE: Ukrainian officials report drone strikes shot down over Kyiv
SUMMARY: Officials in Kyiv, Ukraine, reported a wave of drone strikes against the city late Saturday into Sunday that were intercepted and failed to hit the city.

TITLE: Mets' Luke Voit rocks sleeveless jersey in minors to fans' delight
SUMMARY: Luke Voit has been known to rock his jerseys with the buttons undone, but thanks to the Syracuse Mets' sleeveless look, he took it to a different level in his recent minor league game.

TITLE: Obama's AG weighs in on whether Biden should pardon Trump
SUMMARY: Former Attorney General Eric Holder joined CBS News' "Face the Nation" and discussed if President Biden or the 2024 White House winner should potentially pardon Donald Trump.

TITLE: Biden to meet with King Charles and UK PM Rishi Sunak ahead of NATO summit, White House announces
SUMMARY: President Biden is scheduled to meet with King Charles and U.K. Prime Minister Rishi Sunak to "further strengthen" the countries' relationship before attending the NATO summit.

TITLE: New laws: Here are some of the most impactful bills that took effect across the US on July 1
SUMMARY: From limits on abortion and transgender services to sealing criminal records in California, several major pieces of legislation went into effect on July 1.

TITLE: ABC host presses Dem rep on student loan ruling: SCOTUS 'quoted' Nancy Pelosi
SUMMARY: ABC's Jonathan Karl referenced Nancy Pelosi's position on student loans while pressing Rep. Ro Khanna on the Supreme Court's decision to strike down Biden's plans.

TITLE: New York cop allegedly sent herself menacing texts, then blamed colleagues: prosecutor
SUMMARY: Ossining, New York, police officer Emily Hirshowitz was arrested on criminal charges after allegedly sending herself menacing texts she said were from colleagues.

TITLE: Comedian Gabriel Iglesias' private jet makes emergency landing: ‘Happy to be alive’
SUMMARY: Gabriel Iglesias revealed on his social media that a private jet he was on had to make an emergency landing in North Carolina and skidded off the runway.
